    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#bazama-jmr1978-1979"/>, pp. <citedRange>257-258</citedRange> and pl. LXXXVIa</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>37.1709</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>079600</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="0"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
                    <lb n="1"/><orig>κ</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="2"/><space quantity="1" unit="character"/> <orig>τα</orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="3"/><space quantity="3" unit="character"/> <expan><abbr><am><g type="year">𐅹</g></am></abbr> <ex>ἐτῶν</ex></expan> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
                    <lb n="4"/><space extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> âgé(e) de <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> ans.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> aged <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> years.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> di anni <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>As the upper part of the stele is lost, it is impossible to guess the name of the dead. However, lines 1 and 2, perhaps with other lines missing above, had plausibly
                    the name and father's name of the dead, whereas line 3 has the siglum for 'years', the age being also lost. Nothing was written below. The few surviving letters 
                do not allow to decide whether this inscription should belong to IGCyr or to IRCyr. It was registered here only on behalf of Reynolds' hesitation and would thus be 
                one of the rare instances of the use of the siglum for 'year'.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
